('Brisa Therapeutics feel better in a Breeze', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14827663-L.jpg', 'Jacqueline Rousselow', 'Navigate life’s challenges with expert guidance from real therapists specializing in EMDR trauma therapy. This book is a compassionate companion for anyone seeking self-healing tools to address a wide range of issues, including anxiety, depression, PTSD, chronic pain, addiction, ADHD, relationship struggles, and more. Packed with practical insights, this volume empowers you to: - Overcome triggers and trauma responses. - Build resilience and enhance self-image. - Achieve health, wellness, and improved performance. - Pursue your goals and create a fulfilling life. Whether you’re facing somatic issues, career challenges, or striving for enlightenment, Brisa Therapeutics: Feel Better in a Breeze, Volume 4 provides the tools and support to help you heal, thrive, and dream big. Take the first step toward the life you deserve.', 2024, NOW(), NOW()),
('Health and Physical Education', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/13165590-L.jpg', 'Susan Wilson-Gahan', 'Published in 2012, this work explores themes of Health and Physical Education.', 2012, NOW(), NOW()),
