('Becoming a Healthcare Leader', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10129572-L.jpg', 'Steven B. Reed', 'Published in 2015, this work explores themes of Becoming a Healthcare Leader.', 2015, NOW(), NOW()),
('The 4-Hour Body', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/6673523-L.jpg', 'Timothy Ferriss', 'The 4-Hour Body is the result of an obsessive quest, spanning more than a decade, to hack the human body. It contains the collective wisdom of hundreds of elite athletes, dozens of MDs, and thousands of hours of jaw-dropping personal experimentation. From Olympic training centers to black-market laboratories, from Silicon Valley to South Africa, Tim Ferriss, the #1 New York Times bestselling author of The 4-Hour Workweek, fixated on one life-changing question: For all things physical, what are the tiniest changes that produce the biggest results? Thousands of tests later, this book contains the answers for both men and women.', 2010, NOW(), NOW()),
('Health and Your Body', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/13240161-L.jpg', 'Rebecca Weber', 'Published in 2011, this work explores themes of Health and Your Body.', 2011, NOW(), NOW()),
('Unbearable Lightness', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/6666626-L.jpg', 'Portia de Rossi', 'Known for her roles on the hit TV shows "Ally McBeal" and "Arrested Development," de Rossi delivers a revelatory and searing account of the years she spent secretly suffering from anorexia and bulimia, all the while living under the glare of Hollywood''s bright lights.', 2010, NOW(), NOW()),
('Dying to Be Me', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/7083813-L.jpg', 'Anita Moorjani', '"In this truly inspirational memoir, Anita Moorjani relates how, after fighting cancer for almost four years, her body--overwhelmed by the malignant cells spreading throughout her system--began shutting down. As her organs failed, she entered into an extraordinary near-death experience where she realized her inherent worth. and the actual cause of her disease. Upon regaining consciousness, Anita found that her condition had improved so rapidly that she was able to be released from the hospital within weeks. without a trace of cancer in her body! Within these pages, Anita recounts stories of her childhood in Hong Kong, her challenge to establish her career and find true love, as well as how she eventually ended up in that hospital bed where she defied all medical knowledge. As part of a traditional Hindu family residing in a largely Chinese and British society, she had been pushed and pulled by cultural and religious customs since she had been a little girl. After years of struggling to forge her own path while trying to meet everyone else''s expectations, she had the realization, as a result of her epiphany on the other side, that she had the power to heal herself. and that there are miracles in the Universe that she had never even imagined. In Dying to Be Me, Anita freely shares all she has learned about illness, healing, fear, "being love," and the true magnificence of each and every human being!This is a book that definitely makes the case that we are spiritual beings having a human experience. and that we are all One!"--', 2012, NOW(), NOW()),
('Blackout', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8152026-L.jpg', 'Sarah Hepola', 'A memoir of unblinking honesty and poignant, laugh-out-loud humor, BLACKOUT is the story of a woman stumbling into a new kind of adventure--the sober life she never wanted. Shining a light into her blackouts, she discovers the person she buried, as well as the confidence, intimacy, and creativity she once believed came only from a bottle. Her tale will resonate with anyone who has been forced to reinvent or struggled in the face of necessary change. It''s about giving up the thing you cherish most--but getting yourself back in return.', 2015, NOW(), NOW()),
('Going to the doctor', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8224095-L.jpg', 'Rebecca Rissman', 'Compares the ways people in the nineteenth and twentieth centuries got medical care and the conditions in hospitals with contemporary practices.', 2014, NOW(), NOW()),
('Asexualities', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/7852727-L.jpg', 'Karli June Cerankowski', 'Published in 2014, this work explores themes of Asexualities.', 2014, NOW(), NOW()),
('Heart berries', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10140153-L.jpg', 'Terese Marie Mailhot', 'A powerful, poetic memoir of a woman''s coming of age on the Seabird Island Indian Reservation in the Pacific Northwest. Having survived a profoundly dysfunctional upbringing only to find herself hospitalized and facing a dual diagnosis of post traumatic stress disorder and bipolar II disorder; Terese Marie Mailhot is given a notebook and begins to write her way out of trauma.', 2018, NOW(), NOW()),
('Until I say good-bye', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/11735964-L.jpg', 'Susan Spencer-Wendel', 'A moving and inspirational memoir by celebrated journalist Susan Spencer-Wendel who makes the most of her final days after discovering she has amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS).', 2013, NOW(), NOW()),
('Computer Technology for Health Professionals', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8919207-L.jpg', 'Elio Spinello', 'Published in 2015, this work explores themes of Computer Technology for Health Professionals.', 2015, NOW(), NOW()),
('Read All about the Human Body', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/12403863-L.jpg', 'Claire Throp', 'Published in 2021, this work explores themes of Read All about the Human Body.', 2021, NOW(), NOW()),
('Older yet Faster', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/12523543-L.jpg', 'Keith Bateman', 'Published in 2020, this work explores themes of Older yet Faster.', 2020, NOW(), NOW()),
('Pukka''s promise', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/11371296-L.jpg', 'Ted Kerasote', 'When Ted Kerasote was ready for a new dog after losing his beloved Merle -- who died too soon, as all our dogs do -- he wanted to give his puppy Pukka the longest life possible. But how to do that? So much has changed in the way we feed, vaccinate, train, and live with our dogs from even a decade ago. In an adventure that echoes The Omnivore''s Dilemma with a canine spin, Kerasote tackles those subjects, questioning conventional wisdom and emerging with vital new information that will surprise even the most knowledgeable dog lovers.', 2013, NOW(), NOW()),
('Perfect Health Diet', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/12693379-L.jpg', 'Paul Jaminet', 'Explains simply and clearly how to optimize your diet for a lifetime of great health.', 2010, NOW(), NOW()),
('Intuitive Eating Workbook', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/11102294-L.jpg', 'Evelyn Tribole', 'Published in 2017, this work explores themes of Intuitive Eating Workbook.', 2017, NOW(), NOW()),
('Taste Something New!', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/12913240-L.jpg', 'Jennifer Boothroyd', 'Published in 2016, this work explores themes of Taste Something New!.', 2016, NOW(), NOW()),
('Take a Bath!', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/13924005-L.jpg', 'Gina Bellisario', 'Published in 2014, this work explores themes of Take a Bath!.', 2014, NOW(), NOW()),
('A Life of Wellness', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10385581-L.jpg', 'Daniel Burt', 'Published in 2015, this work explores themes of A Life of Wellness.', 2015, NOW(), NOW()),
('Wheat Belly Total Health', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/9587459-L.jpg', 'William Davis', 'Wheat Belly Total Health answers the question, “What''s next in the battle against wheat?” In his follow-up to the mega bestseller, Wheat Belly, Dr. Davis helps his readers take command over their life and health in the aftermath of wheat. There are many strategies that will help heal the damage caused by years of a wheat-filled diet. And many of these lessons have been learned in the years since the original Wheat Belly was released, lessons played out on the broad public stage of over one million readers, all participating in this grand adventure. Reordering your life after wheat is about learning how to regain full metabolic, gastrointestinal, thyroid, cardiovascular, hormonal, sleep, neurological, bone, and joint health. Understanding the strategies and putting them to use can take health several steps higher, even if the reader has already had a major health success without wheat. In addition to achieving better health in many different areas, life performance also improves in virtually all settings. In the life after wheat, you’ll feel unrestrained, unimpaired, and unstoppable!', 2014, NOW(), NOW()),
('101 ways to get in shape', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8179283-L.jpg', 'Charlotte Guillain', 'Recreational reads that have educational curriculum relevance, including appeal for reluctant girl readers. Each title is full of things to do and offers fun ideas as well as advice on each topic. Fun stories that demonstrate real-life issues will appeal to the reader.', 2011, NOW(), NOW()),
('No Excuses for Your Best Life', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14745072-L.jpg', 'C. A. Gibson', 'Published in 2024, this work explores themes of No Excuses for Your Best Life.', 2024, NOW(), NOW()),
('Brain storms', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10599414-L.jpg', 'Jon Palfreman', '"Seven million people worldwide suffer from Parkinson''s-- with sixty thousand new cases diagnosed each year in the U.S. alone-- and it remains an enigma, with doctors, researchers, and patients hunting for a cure. In Brain Storms, award-winning journalist Jon Palfreman tells their story, a story that takes on urgency when he is diagnosed with the debilitating illness. Palfreman chronicles how scientists have labored to crack the mystery of what was once called ''the shaking palsy,'' from the earliest clinical descriptions to the cutting edge of molecular neuroscience. He charts the victories and setbacks of a massive international effort to best the disease, referred to as one of the best windows into the brain itself."--', 2015, NOW(), NOW()),
('Urban Health', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/9168759-L.jpg', 'Sandro Galea', 'Published in 2010, this work explores themes of Urban Health.', 2010, NOW(), NOW()),
('My love story', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10832329-L.jpg', 'Tina Turner', 'The rock & roll legend examines her illustrious career and complicated personal life, from her darkest hours to her happiest moments.', 2018, NOW(), NOW()),
('A really good day', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/12009388-L.jpg', 'Ayelet Waldman', '"In an effort to treat a debilitating mood disorder, Ayelet Waldman undertook a very private experiment, ingesting 10 micrograms of LSD every three days for a month. This is the story--by turns revealing, courageous, fascinating and funny--of her quietly psychedelic spring, her quest to understand one of our most feared drugs, and her search for a really good day"--', 2017, NOW(), NOW()),
