('Unfuck your brain', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8851486-L.jpg', 'Faith G. Harper', '"Expert advice on the neuroscience of trauma and practical exercises for recovery, written for lay readers"--', 2017, NOW(), NOW()),
('The social cure', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/14379049-L.jpg', 'Jolanda Jetten', '1 volume : 24 cm', 2012, NOW(), NOW()),
('Why Has Nobody Told Me This Before?', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/12821544-L.jpg', 'Julie Smith', 'Drawing on her years of experience as a clinical psychologist, Dr Julie Smith''s first book is a must-have handbook for instantly better mental health. Filled with secrets from the therapy room, Why Has Nobody Told Me This Before? offers simple advice, effective strategies and powerful coping techniques to help readers stay positive and resilient no matter what life throws their way. Written in short, bite-sized entries, in Dr Julie''s warm and informal style, a reader can turn straight to the appropriate section depending on the challenge being faced - and immediately find tools to help. From managing anxiety, dealing with criticism or battling low mood, to building self-confidence, finding motivation or learning to forgive yourself, and much more, this book tackles everyday issues that affect us all and offers easy, practical solutions that might just change your life.', 2022, NOW(), NOW()),
('Yin, yang, yogini', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10825234-L.jpg', 'Kathryn E. Livingston', 'Yin, Yang, Yogini is a memoir about transformation through yoga, with yoga as the backdrop for change, a story of how one can evolve in mid-life and in mid-stride, of how one can learn to let go of the past, let go of fear, and live with trust in the present moment. This is a memoir about a transformational two years of Kathryn''s life, a time in which she learned to trust herself and the universe, even while facing such issues as the death of her parents, her children leaving home for college, panic and anxiety issues, and breast cancer. Kathryn''s story is heartfelt, humorous and timely and about finding courage, strength, and happiness within.', 2014, NOW(), NOW()),
('BodyWHealth', 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/11356372-L.jpg', 'Roddy Carter', 'Published in 2015, this work explores themes of BodyWHealth.', 2015, NOW(), NOW()),
